Drop the regex crate: the compiler's single pattern is the dynamic-gating
directive `^use memo if\(([^\)]*)\)$`, a literal prefix/suffix match. The
regex+regex-automata+regex-syntax stack costs ~130 KB of machine code in the
release binary (even at opt-level="z" and with default features off) — for
one pattern that a strip_prefix/strip_suffix pair expresses exactly. This
also removes the regex hunk previously needed in
0002-baseline-safe-deps.patch.
